headline: Two Reasons Why DPZ is Risky and One Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the last six months, Domino’s shares have sunk to $431, producing a disappointing 18.4% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 10.4% gain. This was partly driven by its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
